I"$<p>The last one of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nerva%E2%80%93Antonine_dynasty#Five_Good_Emperors">Five good emperors</a>, Marcus Aurelius had a note in his <a href="https://amzn.to/2K2gt2L">Meditations</a>: <em>“If you seek tranquillity, do less.”</em> This is one of his thoughts that is the most applicable to software development.
<!--more-->
How many times did you break the code and had you no idea what went wrong? How many changes did you introduce? Would it have been different if you had introduced only one change?</p>
